  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] That's the-- perhaps the, the, the most painful part of, of the testimony because even though I was separated from, from, from my father, my mom, and my brother, this was a-- it happened sudden.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this, this was a physical separation under the worst imaginable circumstances that no human being should be subjected to.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, as you recall, before we took our break, when my dad-- he was asking about the piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this, you know, this haunts me the rest of my life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My-- I told it to a, a therapist one time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and, and he says, Henry, even if you were given-- of you had a loaf of bread, and you, you gave it, would, would you save your father's life?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, maybe.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe I would save him for another day or two or a week.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the fact is, I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and, and, and, yeah, he, he raised me-- he mined coal underground, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 1,000, 2,000 feet under, under, under-- deep level, level underground and worked physically hard, sweat, to, to feed me.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And why couldn't I have, you know, saved even-- and so it was-- In, in defense of it there, the therapist says, but, but you were-- but you were in the same boat.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were in the same shoes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, you didn't-- you didn't have-- All of these are, you know, afterthoughts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the fact is, reasonable to accept that this haunts me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And because I-- this is an opportunity to, to, to, to tell it all, I, I don't hold back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I-- and I tell the most painful moments.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And coming back to that episode, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] this shouldn't happen to no one.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
